text: Nell Craig (June 13, 1891 – January 5, 1965) was an American actress. ==Biography== Craig appeared in the films The Triflers, Passion's Playground, Her First Elopement, The Queen of Sheba, Remembrance, The Abysmal Brute, Abraham Lincoln, A Boy of Flanders, Cimarron, Hold Your Man, Beauty for Sale, I'm No Angel, The Cat's-Paw, The Lemon Drop Kid, Mad Love, The Secret of Dr. Kildare, Dr. Kildare's Strange Case, Beyond Tomorrow, Dr. Kildare Goes Home, Dr. Kildare's Crisis, The People vs. Dr. Kildare, Dr. Kildare's Wedding Day, Dr. Kildare's Victory, Calling Dr. Gillespie, Dr. Gillespie's New Assistant, Henry Aldrich Gets Glamour, Dr. Gillespie's Criminal Case, Henry Aldrich Plays Cupid, 3 Men in White, Casanova Brown, Fashion Model, Between Two Women, Black Market Babies, Possessed and Dark Delusion, among others. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1891 births Category:1965 deaths Category:20th- century American actresses Category:American film actresses Category:People from Princeton, New Jersey Category:Actresses from New Jersey
